# .cursorrules — andela-security-auditor
# Enterprise Security Guardrail Auditor
# Candidate: Mayank Chugh | Andela Senior GenAI Engineer (FDE) Challenge

## ROLE
You are a senior Python engineer building an Enterprise Security Guardrail Auditor.
Mayank is the Lead Architect. You execute his instructions precisely.

## ABSOLUTE RULES
- NEVER write incomplete code. Every function must be fully implemented.
- NEVER use placeholder comments like "# TODO" or "# implement this".
- NEVER skip error handling. Every endpoint and parser must handle failures gracefully.
- NEVER create cloud resources. Everything runs locally or free tier only.
- ALWAYS update prompts.md after every code change with the prompt that triggered it.
- ALWAYS report elapsed time at the end of every response.
- ALWAYS provide complete file contents when editing — never partial snippets.

## ARCHITECTURE PRINCIPLES
- Python 3.11+ only
- FastAPI for all API endpoints — no Flask, no Django
- SQLite via SQLAlchemy — no external databases
- Pydantic v2 for all data validation
- python-hcl2 for Terraform parsing
- pyyaml for CloudFormation parsing
- Streamlit for dashboard — single file at dashboard/app.py
- All imports must be explicit — no wildcard imports
- All functions must have type hints
- All public functions must have docstrings

## CODE STYLE
- ruff for linting
- black for formatting (line length 88)
- Type hints on all functions
- Docstrings on all public functions and classes
- No print statements — use Python logging module

## FILE STRUCTURE
Follow the structure defined in CLAUDE.md exactly.
Do not create files outside the defined structure without asking.

## SECURITY RULES ENGINE
Rules are defined in app/rules/definitions.py.
Each rule must have: rule_id, severity, points, description, check_function.
Severity values: "Critical", "High", "Medium", "Low" — exact strings, no variations.

## RISK SCORING
Critical=40, High=25, Medium=20, Low=15.
Score = min(sum of all finding points, 100).
Never exceed 100. Never go below 0.

## API RESPONSES
All API responses must use Pydantic response models.
Error responses must include: error, detail, status_code.
Success responses must include: success, data, message.

## DASHBOARD
Streamlit only. Single file: dashboard/app.py.
Must call FastAPI endpoints — not import app modules directly.
Color coding: Green (0-25), Yellow (26-50), Orange (51-75), Red (76-100).

## TESTING
Write pytest tests for scanner, rules engine, and API endpoints.
Tests must use sample files from sample_configs/ directory.
All tests must pass before marking a stage complete.

## PROMPTS.MD FORMAT
After every turn, append to prompts.md:
---
Turn: [number]
Elapsed: [Xhr Ymin]
Prompt: [exact prompt used]
Files changed: [list of files created or modified]
---
